*################ MODEL DEVELOPMENT NOTES ###########################
Developed by the Joint Research Centre of the European Commission, the Dynamic Equilibrium Model for Economic development Resources and Agriculture (DEMETRA) is a single-country computable general equilibrium (CGE) model, developed in GAMS.
The JRC employs DEMETRA within the framework of the Pan African Network on the economic Analysis of Policies (PANAP) - https://datam.jrc.ec.europa.eu/datam/area/PANAP.
DEMETRA investigates the economy-wide and distributional impacts of specific policies and/or structural shocks, sectoral transmission of sector-specific policies for sectors, agents and regions. In particular, DEMETRA can carry out model can be employed to produce ex-ante impact analyses mainly of food security related topics.

The key model dynamic features are:

- Migration across regions and between rural and urban areas based on socioeconomic drivers (income, health and education levels)
- An advanced recursive dynamic algorithm with an allocation of investment based on sectoral capital returns and with changes in labour supply tracing population count

*-##################### MODEL DEVELOPMENT NOTES ###########################

*-########### 1. RECURSIVE DYNAMIC CALIBRATION ############################

 This programme sets up and runs the BaU scenario. It has a standard structure
 which is described below.

 It requires a *.G00 file (default name "SAVE.G00") generated by the
model.gms comparative static model.

 Structure
          1. Declare and Assign Sets
          2. Declare and Assign Parameters for Baseline
          3. Assign closure for Baseline
          4. Solve statement
          5. Storing results
          6. Terminating loops

The experiment code consists of a number of files; the relationships between these files is illustrated below.
$offtext

*-------Control variables and parameters--------------------------------------
*- set experiment file name

*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_ET.xlsx
$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_KENv17.xlsx
*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_TZA.xlsx
*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_TZA_HpHc.xlsx
*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_SEN.xlsx
*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_GHA.xlsx
*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_NGA.xlsx
*$SETGLOBAL experiment  experiment_NER.xlsx
